<A>__{he turns the page and discovers his own rough likeness: it's victor's sketch of his patchwork man. the rendering includes suture marks where the pieces were joined. the creature gazes for a long time. his finger traces the penciled suture line where an arm joins the torso. eyes going wider. revelation slowly dawning. no. it can't be. it's too horrible to conceive... ...and he drops the journal, clawing at his coat in a surge of panic, wrenching it away to reveal his arm... and the massive suture scars joining his shoulder to his torso in an exact match to the drawing. he throws his head back in an animalistic primal scream, face twisted in a mask of utter horror, munch's painting made flesh...}
